WEBVTT

00:00:00.000 --> 00:00:03.930
You trust brands you've never bought from. Here's why.

00:00:03.930 --> 00:00:08.930
The brain mistakes recognition for safety. Every exposure leaves a trace.

00:00:08.930 --> 00:00:16.200
Every trace lowers the risk a buyer assigns to your name. Psychologists call it the mere exposure effect.

00:00:16.200 --> 00:00:22.500
Name a brand you'd never question. Now count how many times you saw it before you ever bought.

00:00:22.500 --> 00:00:26.000
Familiarity did the selling long before the product could.

00:00:26.000 --> 00:00:30.130
Trust isn't earned in one impression. It's accumulated.

00:00:30.130 --> 00:00:33.630
Perception and attention intelligence.

00:00:33.630 --> 00:00:40.870
If you want to know how familiar your brand actually is, the audit is free. No pitch. Just arstrategies.com.
